00:37:36.473 --> 00:37:39.780
part.
Other questions?

00:37:39.780 --> 00:37:42.020
All will become clear in due
time.

00:37:42.020 --> 00:37:45.006
Actually, that's not true.
But some things will become

00:37:45.006 --> 00:37:48.310
clear in real time.
Gosh, this was great, excellent.

00:37:48.310 --> 00:37:54.544
All sorts of questions.
So now, let me at least start

00:37:54.544 --> 00:37:57.480
talking about special
relativity.

00:37:57.480 --> 00:38:00.639
There are two kinds of
relativity.

00:38:00.639 --> 00:38:06.680
There's special relativity--and
special relativity,

00:38:06.680 --> 00:38:13.808
which was devised in 1905 by
Einstein--this is essentially a

00:38:13.808 --> 00:38:19.401
set of laws of motion.
So, it's the same thing as

00:38:19.401 --> 00:38:24.116
Newton's Laws of Motion,
only it's a more elaborate

00:38:24.116 --> 00:38:26.723
version of it.
So it substitutes,

00:38:26.723 --> 00:38:28.954
if you will,
for Newton's Laws of Motion,

00:38:28.954 --> 00:38:31.240
and in fact,
incorporates Newton's Laws of

00:38:31.240 --> 00:38:34.314
Motion.
Then there's general

00:38:34.314 --> 00:38:42.130
relativity, discovered about ten
years later, again by Einstein.

00:38:42.130 --> 00:38:46.039
And this is the equivalent of a
law of gravity.

00:38:46.039 --> 00:38:50.900
You'll remember that the way
one has to calculate orbits in

00:38:50.900 --> 00:38:54.249
the Newtonian Theory is,
you take Newton's Law of

00:38:54.249 --> 00:38:56.880
Gravity and you plug it into
Newton's Laws of Motion.

00:38:56.880 --> 00:39:00.222
So, this is a change,
or an enhancement,

00:39:00.222 --> 00:39:03.792
in the laws of motion.
This is a change or an

00:39:03.792 --> 00:39:06.199
enhancement in the law of
gravity.

00:39:06.199 --> 00:39:10.943
In both of these cases – and
this is important to realize –

00:39:10.943 --> 00:39:13.849
it doesn't overturn what Newton
did.

00:39:13.849 --> 00:39:17.199
This is a misconception about
how scientific revolutions work.

00:39:17.199 --> 00:39:21.245
This is as revolutionary a set
of ideas as you could possibly

00:39:21.245 --> 00:39:24.351
imagine.
And yet, Newton's laws

00:39:24.351 --> 00:39:27.659
are--still hold.
They don't overturn them.

00:39:27.659 --> 00:39:30.930
What they do is,
they say, Newton's laws are not

00:39:30.930 --> 00:39:33.853
general laws,
but laws that only operate in

00:39:33.853 --> 00:39:38.488
certain specific situations.
These are now the general laws

00:39:38.488 --> 00:39:42.582
that operate always,
and Newton's calculations are a

00:39:42.582 --> 00:39:47.880
subset of these things that only
work under certain conditions.

00:39:47.880 --> 00:39:51.949
And just to jump ahead a little
bit--the condition is,

00:39:51.949 --> 00:39:55.405
there's a quantity--so,
now I'm going to talk,

00:39:55.405 --> 00:39:58.170
first, about special
relativity.

00:39:58.170 --> 00:40:02.475
We'll leave gravity until later.
But now, let's just talk about

00:40:02.475 --> 00:40:05.573
how things move.
And this is important,

00:40:05.573 --> 00:40:10.931
because this gives rise to the
limit on--to the limit on

00:40:10.931 --> 00:40:14.756
velocity.
All velocities must be left

00:40:14.756 --> 00:40:18.889
less than or equal to the speed
of light.

00:40:18.889 --> 00:40:21.630
You can't go faster than the
speed of light.

00:40:21.630 --> 00:40:26.634
And just to jump ahead,
the way Newton's Laws of Motion

00:40:26.634 --> 00:40:31.361
relate to special relativity is
through a parameter,

00:40:31.361 --> 00:40:37.305
a quantity called gamma [γ].
And this is equal to this

00:40:37.305 --> 00:40:39.710
quantity.
1 - V^(2) /

00:40:39.710 --> 00:40:42.281
c^(2),
the square root of that,

00:40:42.281 --> 00:40:44.659
in the denominator.
Okay.

00:40:44.659 --> 00:40:49.461
1 / (1 - V^(2) /
c^(2))^(1/2) And when

00:40:49.461 --> 00:40:52.833
V is much,
much less than the speed of

00:40:52.833 --> 00:40:56.340
light, then gamma is equal to 1.
You can see.

00:40:56.340 --> 00:40:58.832
If this--if V is much
less than the speed of light,

00:40:58.832 --> 00:41:00.450
this quantity is more or less
zero.

00:41:00.450 --> 00:41:04.619
You got 1 / 1.
Gamma = 1.

00:41:04.619 --> 00:41:08.650
Newtonian physics assumes that
gamma is equal to 1.

00:41:08.650 --> 00:41:12.610
So, this leads directly to all
of Newtonian physics.

00:41:16.909 --> 00:41:20.480
But, as velocities start to get
higher, gamma starts to be

00:41:20.480 --> 00:41:23.530
different from 1.
And if--as V approaches

00:41:23.530 --> 00:41:26.260
the speed of light,
what's going to happen?

00:41:26.260 --> 00:41:28.595
This is going--if V is
the speed of light,

00:41:28.595 --> 00:41:30.590
V^(2) / c^(2)
= 1.

00:41:30.590 --> 00:41:33.873
You've got 1 - 1 in the
denominator, so you've got zero

00:41:33.873 --> 00:41:36.814
in the denominator.
So, as V approaches the

00:41:36.814 --> 00:41:39.200
speed of light,
gamma approaches infinity.

00:41:42.309 --> 00:41:44.942
And then you get--so,
you start to get these

00:41:44.942 --> 00:41:46.350
relativistic effects.

00:41:49.719 --> 00:41:52.665
So, it turns out,
for example,

00:41:52.665 --> 00:41:57.946
in relativistic physics,
that mass isn't exactly what

00:41:57.946 --> 00:42:03.539
Newton thought mass was.
Mass is what's called the rest

00:42:03.539 --> 00:42:07.738
mass;
this is the Newtonian

00:42:07.738 --> 00:42:12.698
mass--times gamma.
So, if everything's moving

00:42:12.698 --> 00:42:15.950
slowly, and gamma = 1,
then the mass is exactly what

00:42:15.950 --> 00:42:18.310
Newton thought it was going to
be.

00:42:18.310 --> 00:42:22.110
It's a property of objects.
It's constant.

00:42:22.110 --> 00:42:25.369
It doesn't change.
Mass is conserved and you can

00:42:25.369 --> 00:42:29.237
do all the wonderful
calculations that you can do in

00:42:29.237 --> 00:42:32.749
Newtonian gravity.
Now, the properties of gamma

00:42:32.749 --> 00:42:36.039
are such--remember this goes to
infinity--that,

00:42:36.039 --> 00:42:40.235
therefore, as the velocity goes
to the speed of light,

00:42:40.235 --> 00:42:44.327
the mass approaches infinity,
because gamma approaches

00:42:44.327 --> 00:42:47.346
infinity.
And you're multiplying the

00:42:47.346 --> 00:42:52.828
Newtonian mass by some number
that's getting larger and larger

00:42:52.828 --> 00:42:58.670
and larger and larger as you get
closer to the speed of light.

00:42:58.670 --> 00:43:02.107
Now, what does this mean?
Remember Newton's Laws of

00:43:02.107 --> 00:43:03.957
Motion.
Let's go all the way back to

00:43:03.957 --> 00:43:08.305
Newton.
This is--force is equal to mass

00:43:08.305 --> 00:43:13.780
times acceleration.
Yeah, go ahead.

00:43:13.780 --> 00:43:18.019
Student: What does gamma
stand for?

00:43:18.019 --> 00:43:20.326
Professor Charles
Bailyn: Gamma is a parameter

00:43:20.326 --> 00:43:22.190
that tells you how relativistic
you are.

00:43:22.190 --> 00:43:32.802
It is defined by this.
So, it's a function of your

00:43:32.802 --> 00:43:34.760
velocity.
Yeah.

00:43:34.760 --> 00:43:39.500
And whether--and how--how much
bigger than 1 it is tells you

00:43:39.500 --> 00:43:43.920
how far away from the Newtonian
Theory relativity is.

00:43:43.920 --> 00:43:48.488
And, the faster you go--the
closer you get to the speed of

00:43:48.488 --> 00:43:53.378
light, the more relativistic you
become and the less Newtonian

00:43:53.378 --> 00:43:56.015
you are.
So, it's a parameter that tells

00:43:56.015 --> 00:43:59.469
you how close you are to Newton.
Other questions, yes?

00:43:59.469 --> 00:44:03.369
Student: How exactly is
gamma derived?

00:44:03.369 --> 00:44:04.188
[inaudible]
Professor Charles

00:44:04.188 --> 00:44:05.139
Bailyn: How was gamma
derived?

00:44:05.139 --> 00:44:08.779
I'll talk about the history of
this next time,

00:44:08.779 --> 00:44:13.551
but basically it was--Einstein
revised the Laws of Motion in

00:44:13.551 --> 00:44:17.795
response to some experiments,
which weren't giving the right

00:44:17.795 --> 00:44:19.830
Newtonian answer.
That's the short version,

00:44:19.830 --> 00:44:21.619
and we'll do the long version
next time.

00:44:21.619 --> 00:44:25.453
And, it was the genius of
Einstein that he recognized how

00:44:25.453 --> 00:44:28.739
it--how the Laws of Motion
should be modified,

00:44:28.739 --> 00:44:31.500
and indeed that they should be
modified at all,

00:44:31.500 --> 00:44:34.619
which was not most other
people's initial reaction to

00:44:34.619 --> 00:44:37.513
these experiments.
Okay, so now,

00:44:37.513 --> 00:44:42.840
what happens if your mass
becomes infinite?

00:44:42.840 --> 00:44:47.659
Right?
That means for a--remember this

00:44:47.659 --> 00:44:50.980
is acceleration,
and this is force.

00:44:50.980 --> 00:44:54.593
If your mass becomes infinite
then F / M,

00:44:54.593 --> 00:44:57.070
which is equal to the
acceleration,

00:44:57.070 --> 00:45:02.940
this goes to zero,
which means you cannot have any

00:45:02.940 --> 00:45:07.851
acceleration,
no matter how much force you

00:45:07.851 --> 00:45:10.267
apply.
And that's why you can't go

00:45:10.267 --> 00:45:12.969
faster than the speed of light.
Right?

00:45:12.969 --> 00:45:16.332
Because as you get closer and
closer to the speed of light,

00:45:16.332 --> 00:45:19.000
this gamma factor becomes
larger and larger.

00:45:19.000 --> 00:45:21.750
That makes your mass larger and
larger.

00:45:21.750 --> 00:45:24.258
And then, to get a given amount
of acceleration,

00:45:24.258 --> 00:45:26.872
since this is huge,
you have to have an increasing

00:45:26.872 --> 00:45:29.726
amount of force.
By the time you get to the

00:45:29.726 --> 00:45:33.506
speed of light the mass
is--sorry, it's this whole thing

00:45:33.506 --> 00:45:37.327
that's zero, not the mass.
By the time you get to the

00:45:37.327 --> 00:45:40.490
speed of light,
you need an infinite amount of

00:45:40.490 --> 00:45:44.413
force to accelerate yourself.
So, you need an infinite amount

00:45:44.413 --> 00:45:48.098
of force in order to go faster.
And so, by the time you get out

00:45:48.098 --> 00:45:50.752
to the speed of light,
you can't go faster,

00:45:50.752 --> 00:45:54.164
because it would take an
infinite amount of force to do

00:45:54.164 --> 00:45:56.480
so.
Yes?

00:45:56.480 --> 00:45:58.022
Student: Does that mean
that when you're traveling the

00:45:58.022 --> 00:45:59.530
speed of light,
not only can you not speed up,

00:45:59.530 --> 00:46:01.563
but you also can't slow down,
since it would take force to

00:46:01.563 --> 00:46:02.777
slow you down?
Professor Charles

00:46:02.777 --> 00:46:04.296
Bailyn: That's right,
and what it really means,

00:46:04.296 --> 00:46:06.521
though,
is that nothing with a non-zero

00:46:06.521 --> 00:46:09.620
mass can actually ever get to
the speed of light.

00:46:09.620 --> 00:46:14.829
And therefore, what about light?
Light has zero mass.

00:46:14.829 --> 00:46:17.260
It has to, otherwise it can't
go at the speed of light.

00:46:17.260 --> 00:46:21.263
So if M_zero
is zero, then this whole thing

00:46:21.263 --> 00:46:25.091
applies in a very different way.
And so anything that goes at

00:46:25.091 --> 00:46:28.296
the speed of light has to be
massless, for just this kind of

00:46:28.296 --> 00:46:30.159
reason.
Yeah?

00:46:30.159 --> 00:46:33.958
Student: If light is
energy then doesn't it have a

00:46:33.958 --> 00:46:35.869
mass equivalent?
Professor Charles

00:46:35.869 --> 00:46:37.834
Bailyn: It has a mass
equivalent, but its rest mass is

00:46:37.834 --> 00:46:41.179
zero.
So, the reason it has energy is

00:46:41.179 --> 00:46:45.139
because you've got zero times
infinity.

00:46:45.139 --> 00:46:48.790
And so, if you slow light down,
then it disappears altogether.

00:46:48.790 --> 00:46:51.690
Right?
Because--if you slow light in a

00:46:51.690 --> 00:46:54.889
vacuum down, I should specify,
it disappears altogether,

00:46:54.889 --> 00:46:57.915
because if this isn't infinite
and this is zero,

00:46:57.915 --> 00:47:00.490
then you've got no mass energy
at all.

00:47:00.490 --> 00:47:03.918
Yes?
Student: If you can't

00:47:03.918 --> 00:47:06.605
accelerate or decelerate,
how do you get to your sort of

00:47:06.605 --> 00:47:08.288
intrinsic velocity?
Professor Charles

00:47:08.288 --> 00:47:09.780
Bailyn: Well,
what is an intrinsic velocity?

00:47:09.780 --> 00:47:12.110
This is where relativity
becomes relative.

00:47:12.110 --> 00:47:16.510
Depends on how fast the person
who's observing you is going.

00:47:16.510 --> 00:47:19.715
But remember,
this only applies if you're

00:47:19.715 --> 00:47:22.840
already moving at the speed of
light.

00:47:22.840 --> 00:47:25.031
If you're not moving at the
speed of light,

00:47:25.031 --> 00:47:28.081
then this isn't infinite.
You have some finite mass and

00:47:28.081 --> 00:47:31.649
you can change your velocity.
Remember, acceleration is a

00:47:31.649 --> 00:47:34.280
change in velocity by applying
force.

00:47:34.280 --> 00:47:37.406
And as long as the mass isn't
infinite, it just--you know,

00:47:37.406 --> 00:47:39.599
you calculate how much force it
takes.

00:47:39.599 --> 00:47:41.580
And that's how much it takes to
change your velocity.

